GET CERTIFICATE: Project Management Essentials Certified

Question 1) The States of Managing a Project:

This stage includes the review and tracking of the progress and quality of work being done.

  • Closing
  • Executing
  • Planning
  • Monitoring

Question 2) The States of Managing a Project:

The process to bring closure to the project for stakeholders by the organization. 

  • Monitoring
  • Planning
  • Closing
  • Executing

Question 3) Which Characteristics of failure does this represent:

“Bad planning and coordination of resources that leads to suboptimal projects”

  • Clear objectives
  • Poor Scheduling
  • Business Case
  • Communication Issue

Question 4) Project management is accomplished using ______ process groups

  • 10
  • 5
  • 8
  • 3

Question 5) At what stage during a project is the project charter generally created?

  • initiating
  • Closing
  • Planning
  • Monitoring

Question 6) The Stages of Managing a Project:

This stage includes the general activities used in preparation to deploy and activate the project.

  • Closing
  • Monitoring
  • Initiating
  • Planning

Question 7) Projects are generally considered to have the following characteristic:

  • Product based
  • Result-oriented
  • Open-ended
  • Stakeholder focused

Question 8) Projects usually have finite resources.

  • False
  • True

Question 9) To become a good project manager, it is important to know how projects can _______.

  • Fail
  • Improve operations
  • Reduce Waste
  • Reduce Payroll

Question 10) The Stages of Managing a Project:

This stage includes the actual performance of work activities to meet the project requirements.

  • Monitoring
  • Closing
  • Initiating
  • Executing

Question 11) Which Characteristic of failure does this represent:

“Working on a project only to realize that the market has vanished or that the project is no longer beneficial to the company.”

  • Business Case
  • Poor scheduling
  • Clear objectives
  • Communication issue

Question 12) Which Characteristic of      ure does this represent:

“The team needs to know exactly what they are trying to achieve and clients need to know exactly what they are going to receive.”

  • Poor scheduling
  • Clear objectives
  • Business Case
  • Communications issue

Question 13) Which Characteristic of failure does this represent:

“Inefficient communication between anyone who has interests in the project can be disastrous.”

  • Business Case
  • Poor scheduling
  • Clear objectives
  • Communications issue

Question 14) Which Characteristic of failure does this represent:

“A project can go over budget when unforeseen circumstances deplete the allocated resources and there is no clear contingency or backup plan.”

  • Vague Progress
  • Resource Estimation
  • Quality
  • Vague Responsibility

Question 15) Projects are considered:

  • Necessary but undesirable
  • Temporary Endeavors
  • Permanent Endeavors
  • A drain on resources

Question 16) “It is critical to know the end quantifiable objective so progress can be measured against the goal.”

  • Vague Progress
  • Quality
  • Resource Estimation
  • Vague Responsibility

Question 17) The Stages of Managing a Project:

The beginning phase of a project, taking it from a concept to an actual starting point.

  • Closing
  • Executing
  • Initiating
  • Planning
